cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CC 

The paper discusses fundamental concepts in information theory and their relevance to neuroscience, specifically computational neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses information theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence of information theory and neuroscience, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper could also fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the complexity of neuronal networks.
